rComments: This is a very heavy class so if you're not into molecular biology you're gonna have a hard time. It was her first time teaching online, and her teaching format was to post powerpoints with audio. I don't think it's her fault that her lectures are heavy - this is what you should expect from this type of class.

This course is extremely interesting (though heavy) and she made it unbearable. Her lectures were so long, very boring (monotonous voice). If i was having trouble sleeping, I'd probably put one of her lectures on to help me sleep. Her exams were MCQ, 2 long answer and the grading scheme is very specific for the long answer...u won't get full marks

AVOID AT ALL COST. She sounded lost, depressed and suck out all the life of this course, which could have been very interesting. As a director or a teacher, she talked in the back of her TAs saying that they were depressed and responsible for the bad marking when she is responsible for the harsh grading. Not to mention the 3h long lecture, not 1h20

Dr. Laneuville is a good prof. It was obvious that she was trying to get adjusted to online teaching. Her lectures were definitely long sometimes, but it showed that she was trying to get adjusted. Exams were not easy but fair. She was available every week to go over things that weren't clear.

One of the worst profs I've had in my undergrad. Classes are 3 hours instead of 1h20, EVERY WEEK. Tests are very hard. Even if you study hard, you're gonna have a tough time in her class. There is a lot of material and you need to know every detail. Questions are tricky. She does not listen to suggestions the students make about her teaching.

1) worse prof of the Faculty of Science 2) she abuses of the teaching time. classes are 3h00 instead of 1h20 3) the content would be fun to learn if she was actually good. 4) so monotonous and NOT entertaining all all 5) would give a 0 if it was possible.

Dr. Laneuville was a fantastic prof and BIO4115 was interesting and relatively easy to do well in. There's also no final exam, and the midterms are not cumulative. If you get the chance to take her class take it in a heartbeat, she's a gem

I took the course Topics Chosen in Molecular Biology and it was amazing. There was about 5 people in the course and it made things feel more personal. She explains concepts very well and has VERY clear expectations for the tests, written report and oral presentation. Definitely take this course with her if you have the chance.
Terrible professor. Zero empathy.

I was intimidated to take this class cause I had Odette for mol bio in 3rd year, but I loved this course with her. She gave a complete breakdown for both midterms so you knew exactly what to study. 2 midterms and a term presentation and paper instead of a final, which I think were relatively easy. Definitely would recommend!

Didn't give any marks back until after the final. Also didn't give any feedback/rubrics so hard to know how you could have done better. Has no office hours but says she's "available" outside of class. Doesn't respond to emails/ignores them unless they're easy to answer. Low key played favourites. Overall, wouldn't recommend.

Not a great lecturer - she talks too fast and her powerpoints are very confusing, but you can tell she's a very nice person. She didn't give us any videos, so it made it pretty hard to understand her hectic ppts.

Dr. Laneuville is a great professor. Her tests are very fair and the questions she asks are clear. She doesn't give any surprise questions on stuff she hasn't mentioned in class, but that being said you have to make sure you copy down what she is saying in class. She is very helpful outside of lectures as well on anything you might need.

She is a caring prof... makes excellent learning objective videos which closely reflect midterm and exam questions. Her test are non-cummulatative. The class is broken down into 30% for each midterm (2) and 60% final exam

Your grade is based off 2 midterms and a final. The long answer Qs are basically identical to her learning objectives & the multiple choice were a bit more difficult (you needed to take notes in class to capture those details). The marking schemes were tough but she gave extra marks in the end. Super funny as a person and her research seems awesome

Her lectures are kind of hard to follow as she's not the best at explaining concepts. However, she does a great job with the learning objective videos. The midterms and final were extremely fair. She asks questions similar to the learning objectives in the long answer but a little more detail in the multiple choice.

Not the best lecture (she talks way too fast), but he's learning objective videos are a must! Study off them for the midterms and final because those will be the questions she asks. The material is really dense and there is a lot of little details that you have to remember, but the evaluations are non-cumulative! #Mechanisssssmsss
Very fair. If you got something wrong, it was your fault. She gives everything you need to do well.

At first I really did not like her lectures. She speaks very quickly and may contradict herself and ends class early. However, the videos posted on BB are great summaries of the material taught, but do not depend on those for midterms. You must know every detail and read questions carefully. Her MC were tricky but long and short answers were easy.

Lectures were pretty boring and sometimes not very organized, but the videos she pots on blackboard summarize 90% of what she wants you to know for exams. Occasionally makes jokes in class, and ends class early.

Odette taught the first half of the course. She has a really tough marking scheme on midterms and final. Make sure you do the videos, they are pretty much recaps of lectures and the short answers on her exams. She's hilarious tho. Enjoy Odette because Luc's part is scary and I would much rather Odette than Elaine Beaulieu (BIO3120).

Dr. Laneuville is extremely clear in what she expects you to know to do well on each of her midterms. She assigns "Learning Objectives" to which there are accompanying videos of here explaining major concepts. Know these inside and out and you will do extremely well. Tough content, but work hard and an A+ is attainable.

Her objectives videos, which is a must, do not match her notes and she rarely answers the question. Very unclear with what she wants on her midterms. Lectures are all over the place and loaded with paragraph of information. Would not recommend.
Great Prof, just make sure you take detailed notes in class.

Horrible professor. Has a heavy french accent that makes it difficult to understand what she is saying. Lots of bad jokes in an attempt to cover up inability to make material interesting. Lectures are loaded with detailed information and she talks fast so you might as well study on your own. Very unhelpful and rude.
Has very clear expectations. Excellent and articulate lecturer. Videos are a must for her midterms. Pretty detail oriented so understand and then memorize, memorize, memorize.

In lecture she goes really fast, and it may seem confusing, but her videos and notes are stellar! One of the very few profs who actually teaches you EXACTLY what she expects you to know. Her videos are word for word her shortlong answer questions, so study those. It is a shame she doesn't teach the whole course. Excellent prof, very helpful.

Rigid marking schemes, for some reason I always felt she was really picky in all the details that you had to have written on your exam to get the marks based on the marking scheme. She is straight-forward but even if you memorize the answers you won't get the full marks because of the marking scheme. She is nice in person though.

She is a good professor in that it is extremely clear what she will test you on. Take the time to really study her notes! Her videos are literally word for word all her long answer questions on exams. No textbook req'd

Probably the most straightforward science professor I've ever had. She teaches exactly what she asks you to know for the exam and she is very good at explaining the material. Her YouTube videos are great! The only thing to watch for here is completeness of your answers. She will mark hard if you miss small details here and there.

The most insanely helpful notes I've ever used. Extremely clear, extremely easy to use. I was sick for almost all of the classes taught, and I feel I have a better understanding of the material she taught, simply by having read her notes, (as well as the INCREDIBLY helpful Youtube videos she provides) than I had with any other profs.
Boring teacher. Hard exams.
Very clear. Not too difficult, especially when compared to some of the other profs for molecular bio. Listen to what she says and you'll be fine.

Well, at least she's very clear about what she wants you to know - make sure you memorize your slides, word for word.  ALL OF THEM.  Don't bother sending her emails asking for help - she'll send you back a useless one-word answer, or nothing at all.  Hates seeing students outside of class.

Not approachable/helpful out of class (as in downright insulting) Thank god she told us questions that would be on exams because she is tough. If you ask her to clarify during the exam she will purposely steer you wrong.

I liked her. She explains pretty well in class, and tells you in advance some of what will be on the exam. Her exam questions are hard but if you've memorized everything (keyword: MEMORIZE) they are very feasible. One good thing about her is she's really fair when marking: if the class average is too low she isn't afraid of adding points.

Her exam questions are so twisted. Full of double negatives and positives. Can never figure out what she's asking. Her MC questions are 3 marks each and they are very hard. She's very unfriendly and doesn't seem to like being a prof. She also talks lowly of the medical profession...she seems envious.

Quite decent teacher, explains fairly well in class, but her multiple choice exam questions are brutal! Only major complaint is that she took almost 3 weeks to return midterms, way beyond the faculty-specified 10 days, that was a huge p***off
When she says, "This is on the exam!" she means it. She was awesome!
Exam questions are so convoluted, it's difficult to figure out what she's asking
